# mise

`mise` manages language runtimes, environment variables, and tasks per project,
reproducibly (successor to asdf-style version managers).

## Running a managed dependency

- A tool installed/pinned by `mise` may not be on bare `PATH`. To run it, prefix the
  command with `mise x -- <command>`, or invoke the project's `mise` task, so the
  correct version and project environment apply.
- This is the canonical resolver for "how do I actually run this dependency?" — other
  skills (`my-linting`, `my-testing`, `my-coding-python`) reference here instead of
  hardcoding a `mise x --` prefix.

## Tasks & env

- Prefer a defined `mise` task (`mise run <task>`) when the project provides one.
- mise supplies per-project env vars; don't replicate them with ad-hoc exports.
